        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 3:12PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northwest of Bodfish, or 32 miles southeast of Porterville,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Isabella, Glennville, and Uhl.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
